# ✍️ Content SEO Rules

## Content Brief Template

When creating or reviewing content, always generate a brief:

```markdown
## Content Brief: {Title}

**Target URL**: /path/to/page/
**Primary Keyword**: {keyword} ({monthly searches} searches/mo)
**Secondary Keywords**: {kw1}, {kw2}, {kw3}
**Search Intent**: Informational / Commercial / Transactional
**Content Type**: Guide / List / Review / Landing Page / Product
**Target Word Count**: {number} (based on top 3 competitors avg)

**SERP Features to Target**:
- [ ] Featured Snippet (answer box)
- [ ] People Also Ask
- [ ] Image Pack
- [ ] Video Carousel
- [ ] Local Pack

**Content Outline**:
H1: {Primary keyword + modifier}
  H2: {Main section 1}
    H3: {Subsection}
  H2: {Main section 2}
  H2: FAQ (for PAA keywords)

**Internal Links TO add**: {related pages to link to}
**Internal Links FROM**: {pages that should link here}
**CTA**: {primary conversion goal}
```

## Heading Hierarchy Rules

```markdown
<!-- ✅ Correct -->
# Primary Keyword: Complete Guide (H1 — one per page)
## What is {Topic}? (H2 — main sections)
### Types of {Topic} (H3 — subsections)
#### Specific Type Details (H4 — rarely needed)

<!-- ❌ Wrong -->
# Title
### Skipped H2 (never skip levels)
## Back to H2
# Another H1 (never use multiple H1s)
```

**H1 Rules**:
- Exactly ONE per page
- Contains primary keyword (naturally)
- Under 60 characters ideally
- Matches or closely mirrors title tag
- Compelling to humans, not just keyword-stuffed

**H2 Rules**:
- Use for major sections
- Include secondary/related keywords naturally
- Questions make great H2s (target PAA)
- Minimum 300 words of content per H2

## URL Structure

```
✅ Good URLs:
/pilates-studio/
/pilates-studio/mat-pilates-classes/
/blog/pilates-benefits-for-back-pain/

❌ Bad URLs:
/page?id=123
/pilates-studio/page1/subpage2/category/article-name/
/PILATES-STUDIO/ (uppercase)
/pilates_studio/ (underscores)
/pilates-studio-best-pilates-studio-classes/ (keyword stuffing)
```

**URL Rules**:
- Use hyphens (-) not underscores (_)
- Lowercase only
- Short and descriptive (3–5 words max)
- Include primary keyword
- No stop words unless needed for clarity
- End with slash for consistency (pick one and stick to it)
- Avoid dates in URLs for evergreen content

## Image SEO

```html
<!-- ✅ Optimized image -->
<img 
  src="/images/pilates-reformer-class-beginner.webp"
  alt="Beginner Pilates Reformer class at Lumina Studio with instructor"
  title="Pilates Reformer for Beginners"
  width="800" 
  height="533"
  loading="lazy"        <!-- lazy for below-fold, eager for above-fold -->
  decoding="async"
  srcset="/images/pilates-reformer-400.webp 400w,
          /images/pilates-reformer-800.webp 800w,
          /images/pilates-reformer-1200.webp 1200w"
  sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 800px"
>

<!-- ❌ Bad image SEO -->
<img src="/img/IMG_20240115_001.jpg" alt="image">
```

**Image Optimization Checklist**:
- [ ] Descriptive filename (keyword-phrase.webp)
- [ ] Alt text describes image + includes keyword when natural
- [ ] WebP or AVIF format (fallback JPG/PNG)
- [ ] Compressed (use Squoosh, TinyPNG, or imagemin)
- [ ] Explicit width and height (prevents CLS)
- [ ] Lazy load below fold, eager load above fold
- [ ] Responsive srcset for different viewports

## Internal Linking Strategy

### Hub and Spoke Model
```
Pillar Page: "Complete Pilates Guide"
├── Spoke: "Mat Pilates for Beginners"
├── Spoke: "Pilates Equipment Explained"
├── Spoke: "Pilates Benefits for Back Pain"
├── Spoke: "Prenatal Pilates Guide"
└── Spoke: "Pilates vs Yoga Comparison"

All spokes link BACK to pillar.
Pillar links OUT to all spokes.
Spokes cross-link to related spokes.
```

### Anchor Text Rules
```
✅ Good anchor text:
- Descriptive: "learn more about mat pilates classes"
- Keyword-rich: "pilates exercises for back pain"
- Natural: "as we covered in our Reformer guide"

❌ Bad anchor text:
- Generic: "click here", "read more", "this article"
- Over-optimized: "best pilates studio classes near me cheap"
- Bare URL: "https://example.com/pilates/"
```

## E-E-A-T Signals

Incorporate these to improve trustworthiness:

### Experience
```markdown
- First-person accounts: "In our studio, we've seen..."
- Original photos and videos (not stock)
- Case studies with real client stories
- Personal testing and results
```

### Expertise
```markdown
- Author bio with credentials and photo
- Sources cited (studies, .gov, .edu, authoritative sites)
- Accurate, detailed information
- Technical depth appropriate to audience
- Regular content updates with dates
```

### Authoritativeness
```markdown
- External links to and from authority sites
- Expert quotes and interviews
- Industry awards and certifications mentioned
- Press coverage and mentions
- Verified business information
```

### Trustworthiness
```markdown
- HTTPS everywhere
- Privacy policy, terms of service
- About page with team and contact info
- Clear editorial guidelines
- No misleading claims
- Medical/legal content reviewed by professionals
```

## Readability Standards

```
Flesch-Kincaid Grade Level:
- General audience: 6–8
- Technical/B2B: 8–12
- Academic: 12+

Sentence Rules:
- Average: 15–20 words
- Max: 30 words before breaking
- Variety: mix short punchy sentences with longer ones

Paragraph Rules:
- Max 3–4 sentences for web content
- One idea per paragraph
- White space is your friend

Formatting for Scan-Ability:
- Use bullet points for 3+ items
- Bold key terms and takeaways
- Use tables for comparisons
- Add TL;DR at the top for long posts
- Include a table of contents for 1500+ word articles
```

## Content Freshness Strategy

```markdown
## When to Update Content
- Traffic drops 20%+ over 3 months
- Rankings slip for target keywords
- Factual information becomes outdated
- Competitor content is more comprehensive
- Statistics/data are older than 2 years

## How to Update
1. Add "Last Updated: {Date}" to front matter/post
2. Update statistics and outdated facts
3. Add new sections for topics competitors cover
4. Improve existing sections with more depth
5. Add new internal links to recent content
6. Update meta description if CTR is low
7. Submit to Google via GSC URL Inspection

